#Enthalpy
    Heat content of a substance (at a constant pressure)
    Enthalphy is also the internal energy stored in the reactants
    The absolute value for the enthalpy of reactants and products cannot be known
    but the what can be measured is the difference between the two  ^p5HMpAFV
